Add an Emacs Lisp helper in rb-tools.el (e.g. `rb-tools-bash-eval`) that accepts a single non-empty script string, runs it via `bash -lc <script>` using `process-file`, and captures stdout/stderr in temp buffers. The helper should return a plist like `(:exit_code n :stdout "..." :stderr "...")`, normalize any trailing newlines consistently, and raise a helpful error when the script argument is missing or `bash` cannot be executed.